## SSH Brute Force Detector (Version 2)

This is the second version of the **SSH Brute Force Detector**.

The application analyzes SSH authentication logs and detects potential brute-force attacks by counting failed login attempts from each IP address within a specified time window.

### Features

- Detects failed SSH login attempts per IP address.
- Configurable time window (default: **10 minutes**).
- Configurable minimum number of failed attempts required to report an IP address.
- Reports the time range in which the failed attempts occurred.
- Counts and displays the number of skipped (invalid) log lines.

## Usage

bash
python3 main.py <path_to_log> <time_window> <minimum_failed_attempts>


### Arguments

| Argument | Description |
|----------|-------------|
| `path_to_log` | Path to the SSH log file |
| `time_window` | Time period (in minutes) to analyze (default: 10) |
| `minimum_failed_attempts` | Minimum number of failed login attempts required to report an IP |

## Example

python3 main.py auth.log 10 5


### Example Output

Test has been done. Settings: Period to check is 10 minutes; Failed target to detect is 5
IP: 100.10.100.10 | Failed attemps: 14 | Analyzed since: 08.07.2026 23:00:00 to 08.07.2026 23:04:20
IP: 200.20.200.20 | Failed attemps: 6 | Analyzed since: 08.07.2026 23:02:41 to 08.07.2026 23:03:11
IP: 210.20.210.20 | Failed attemps: 6 | Analyzed since: 08.07.2026 23:10:00 to 08.07.2026 23:10:20
Skipped lines: 8



